name: Argostars – Courageous Arion
desc:
2 Level 4 monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name each once per turn. Once per turn, you can also Xyz Summon "Argostars – Courageous Arion" by using 1 "Argostars" monster you control (transfer its materials to this card).
①: If this card is Xyz Summoned: You can add 1 "Argostars" Spell from your Deck to your hand.
②: During the Standby Phase: You can detach 2 materials from this card; place up to 3 "Argostars" Continuous Traps from your GY, face-up in your Spell & Trap Zone.

name: Prima Light
desc:
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①: Activate 1 of these effects;
● Tribute 1 EARTH Warrior monster, and if you do, Special Summon 1 LIGHT Warrior monster from your hand or Deck.
● During the Main Phase: Immediately after this effect resolves, Normal Summon 1 Warrior monster from your hand.
②: During your Main Phase: You can banish this card from your GY; add 1 Warrior or Fairy "Cyber" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Legend of Justice Kaibaman
desc:
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can show 3 "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" in your hand, Deck, face-up field, and/or GY, then Special Summon 1 "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" from your hand, Deck, or GY.
②: If you Special Summoned "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" while this card is in your GY (except during the Damage Step): You can banish this card; add 1 "Blue-Eyes" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Gaia Stream, the Graceful Force
desc:
2+ Level 6 monsters
Once per turn, you can also Xyz Summon "Gaia Stream, the Graceful Force" by using 1 Rank 5 or 7 Xyz Monster you control (transfer its materials to this card). Cannot be used as material for an Xyz Summon the turn it was Xyz Summoned.
①: Cannot attack directly.
②: Gains ATK equal to the combined Levels/Ranks of its attached materials x 200.
③: At the end of the Damage Step, if this card battles: Detach 1 material from this card.

name: Conduction Warrior Linear Magnum ±
desc:
Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must first be Special Summoned (from your hand) by sending 2 "Magnet Warrior" monsters whose original Level is 4 or lower from your hand, Deck, and/or face-up field to the GY. You can only Special Summon "Conduction Warrior Linear Magnum ±" once per turn this way. You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can target 1 other EARTH monster on the field; this card gains ATK equal to half that monster's until the end of this turn.
②: If this card is destroyed and sent to the GY: Add it to your hand.

name: Chaos Distill
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: Any card sent to your GY is banished instead.
②: You can activate 1 of these effects;
● Add 1 "Macro Cosmos", or 1 card that mentions it, from your Deck to your hand, except "Chaos Distill".
● If "Macro Cosmos" is on the field: Banish this face-up card from the Spell & Trap Zone; add 1 LIGHT monster with ? ATK from your Deck to your hand.

name: Hero's Rule 1: Five Freedoms
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: Target up to 5 cards in any GY(s); banish them.
②: If this card is in your GY, except the turn it was sent there: You can banish it, then target 1 of your banished "Elemental HERO" monsters; Special Summon it, ignoring its Summoning conditions.

name: Archfiend Matador
desc:
You can Ritual Summon this card with "Ritual of the Matador". You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If this card is Ritual Summoned: You can add 2 "Archfiend" cards from your Deck to your hand, except "Archfiend Matador", also this card cannot attack this turn.
②: Cannot be destroyed by battle, also you take no battle damage from battles involving this card.
③: If this card battles a monster, after damage calculation: Destroy that monster, and if you do, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

name: Ritual of the Matador
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: Ritual Summon 1 "Archfiend Matador" from your hand, by Tributing monsters from your hand and/or field whose total Levels equal 6 or more.
②: You can banish this card from your GY; Special Summon 1 non-Ritual "Archfiend" monster from your hand.

name: Morgana the Witch of Eyes
desc:
(This card is always treated as a "Morganite" card.)
You can only use the ① and ③ effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can add 1 "Morganite" Spell from your Deck to your hand.
②: When an opponent's monster declares an attack: You can banish 1 "Morganite" Spell from your GY; negate that attack.
③: If you have 3 or more "Morganite" Spells with different names in your GY and/or banishment: You can make the ATK of all face-up monsters your opponent controls to 0.

name: Guilt Gripping Morganite
desc:
①: For the rest of this Duel, apply the following effects.
●You cannot activate monster effects in the hand.
●You can Normal Summon Level 5 or higher monsters without Tributing.
●You do not pay LP to activate Spell/Trap Cards.
②: You can banish this card from your GY, then reveal 1 "Morganite" card in your hand; place the revealed card on the bottom of the Deck, then draw 1 card.

name: Medius the Innocent
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can take 1 "Imprisoned Deity" monster from your Deck and either add it to your hand or Special Summon it.
②: If this card is in your GY: You can shuffle 1 monster from your hand or face-up field into the Deck, and if you do, Special Summon this card, but banish it when it leaves the field.

name: Artmegia Finemelt
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If you control an "Artmegia" card: You can Special Summon this card from your hand, then you can draw 1 card.
②: Your opponent cannot target Level 6 or lower "Artmegia" monsters you control with card effects.
③: During the Main Phase, if you control 3 or more Monster Types (Quick Effect): You can negate the effects of all face-up monsters your opponent currently controls, also their current ATK become halved until the end of this turn.

name: Artmegia Graphlare
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If you control an "Artmegia" card: You can Special Summon this card from your hand, then you can Set 1 "Artmegia" Spell from your Deck.
②: The first time this card card would be destroyed by battle each turn, it is not destroyed.
③: You can target 1 Spell/Trap your opponent controls; destroy it. This is a Quick Effect if you control 3 or more Monster Types.

name: Artmegia Litera
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If you control an "Artmegia" card: You can Special Summon this card from your hand, then you can add 1 "Artmegia" card from your GY to your hand.
②: You take no battle damage from battles involving this card.
③: During your opponent's Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can Special Summon 1 "Artmegia" monster from your hand or GY, except "Artmegia Litera", then return this card on the field to the hand.

name: Imprisoned Deity Beast of Artmegia
desc:
You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck, except Fusion Monsters.
②: During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can Fusion Summon 1 "Artmegia" Fusion Monster or "Nerva the Imprisoned Deity of Creation" from your Extra Deck, using monsters from your hand or field, including this card you control.
③: If this card is sent from the hand or field to the GY: You can add 1 "Artmegia" Spell/Trap from your Deck to your hand with a different name from the cards in your GY.

name: Artmegia Diaktoros
desc:
"Medius the Innocent" + 1 "Artmegia" monster
You can only use the ①, ②, and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can target 1 monster on the field; change its battle position.
②: When your opponent activates a card or effect on the field and you control 3 or more Monster Types (Quick Effect): You can negate the activation, and if you do, destroy that card.
③: If this Fusion Summoned card is destroyed: You can Special Summon 1 "Medius the Innocent" from your hand, Deck, or banishment.

name: Nerva the Imprisoned Deity of Creation
desc:
3 "Artmegia" monsters
Must first be either Fusion Summoned, or Special Summoned (from your Extra Deck) in Defense Position by Tributing 3 monsters with different Types. You can only Special Summon "Nerva the Imprisoned Deity of Creation" once per turn.
①: Cannot be destroyed by card effects while there is a card in the Field Zone.
②: Once per turn, when you activate an "Artmegia" monster's effect (Quick Effect): You can make that effect become "Destroy all cards your opponent controls".

name: Artmegia the Academy City of Divine Arts
desc:
①: During your Main Phase, you can Normal Summon 1 "Medius the Innocent" in addition to your Normal Summon/Set. (You can only gain this effect once per turn.)
②: You can discard 1 Spell/Trap and declare the name of 1 "Artmegia" monster you do not control; add 1 of the declared monster from your Deck to your hand, also you cannot Special Summon from outside the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except "Artmegia" monsters and "Medius the Innocent". 
(You can only declare each card name once per turn to activate this effect of this card's name.)

name: Theorealize
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: Send 1 "Medius the Innocent" from your Deck to the GY; look at the top card of your opponent's Deck and place it on either the top or bottom of the Deck.
②: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 face-up monster you control and declare 1 Monster Type and 1 Attribute; it becomes the declared Type and Attribute until the end of your opponent's turn.

name: Artmegia Masterwork – Succession
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: During the Main Phase: Fusion Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, using monsters from your hand or field, including an "Artmegia" monster, then, if there is a card in the Field Zone, the Summoned monster gains 500 ATK.
②: During your Main Phase: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 3 "Artmegia" cards in your GY with different names; shuffle them into the Deck.

name: Artmegia Vandalism – Assault
desc:
You can only activate 1 card with this card's name per turn. You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: When this card resolves, you can add 1 "Medius the Innocent" from your Deck to your hand.
②: You can target 1 face-up monster you control; that face-up monster can be treated as an "Artmegia" monster if used as Fusion Material this turn.
③: If "Artmegia the Academy City of Divine Arts" you control would be destroyed by card effect, you can send this card you control to the GY instead.

name: Artmegia Banish – Change
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: Place 1 "Artmegia the Academy City of Divine Arts" from your Deck or GY face-up in your Field Zone, or, if you control it, you can add 1 "Artmegia" card from your Deck to your hand instead, except "Artmegia Banish – Change".
②: When your "Artmegia" monster is targeted for an attack: You can banish this card from your GY; negate that attack, then you can Special Summon 1 "Medius the Innocent" from your hand.

name: Artmegia Messena – Awakening
desc:
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①: Special Summon 1 "Artmegia" monster or "Medius the Innocent" from your Deck, also, this turn, the activation of your cards and effects that include an effect that Fusion Summons a Fusion Monster cannot be negated, also your opponent cannot activate cards or effects when a monster is Fusion Summoned this way.
②: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 "Artmegia" monster you control; return it to the hand/Extra Deck, and if you do, destroy 1 card your opponent controls.

name: Ukanomitsune-no-Onari
desc:
2 LIGHT monsters, including a Beast monster
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Link Summoned: You can target 1 Quick-Play Spell in your GY; Set it.
②: Your opponent cannot target cards in the Field Zones with card effects.
③: If this card is destroyed: You can choose the following effects up to the number of cards in the Field Zones and apply them in sequence (you cannot choose the same effect twice).
● Destroy 1 card your opponent controls.
● Inflict 1500 damage to your opponent.

name: Sacramentum Dragoon
desc:
1 Dragon monster + 1 Spellcaster monster
You can only use the ③ effect of this card's name once perturn.
①: Loses 100 ATK for each of your banished cards.
②: Your opponent's Special Summoned Dragon and Spellcaster monsters cannot activate their effects while this Fusion Summoned card is in the Monster Zone.
③: You can target 1 Dragon and 1 Spellcaster monster in your GY; Special Summon 1 of them, and if you do, place the other on the bottom of the Deck.

name: Vallon, the Psychic Skyblaster
desc:
2 Level 5 monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①: During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can detach 1 material from this card, then target 1 face-up monster your opponent controls; change it to face-down Defense Position.
③: If this card is sent to the GY: You can target 1 Set card; destroy it.

name: Prototype Sky Striker Ace – Amatsu
desc:
1 "Sky Striker Ace" monster
You can only Special Summon "Protoype Sky Striker Ace – Amatsu" once per turn. You can only use this card name's ① and ② effects once per turn each.
①: When a monster your opponent controls with 2000 or more ATK activates its effect (Quick Effect): You can make that effect become "Destroy 1 "Sky Striker Ace" Link Monster your opponent controls." instead.
②: When an attack is declared involving this card and an opponent's monster: You can target 1 "Sky Striker Ace" monster you control and 1 card your opponent controls; destroy them.

name: Inferno of the Ashened
desc:
You can only activate 1 card with this card's name per turn. You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: When this card resolves, you can place 1 "Obsidim, the Ashened City" from your Deck face-up in either Field Zone.
②: You can target 1 face-up card your opponent controls and 1 Level 8 or higher DARK Pyro monster in your GY; send that card on the field to the GY, and if you do, Special Summon that other monster from your GY to your opponent's field in Defense Position.

name: Miasma Dragon Tistina
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can add 1 "Tistina" monster from your Deck to your hand, except "Miasma Dragon Tistina", also LIGHT “Tistina” monsters you control will gain 1000 ATK for the rest of this turn.
②: If this card is sent to the GY and a card is in the Field Zone: You can Special Summon this card, also you cannot Special Summon from the hand or GY for the rest of this turn, except "Tistina" monsters.

name: Dark Flare Swordsman
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can send 1 "Flame Swordsman" or 1 monster that mentions it from your Extra Deck to the GY; Special Summon this card from your hand, also you cannot declare attacks for the rest of this turn, except with Warrior monsters.
②: You take no damage from battles involving this card.
③: (Quick Effect): You can Tribute this card; Special Summon 1 monster that mentions "Flame Swordsman" from your Deck, except a Level 6 monster.

name: Spring
desc:
①: Once per turn: You can choose any number of your unused Main Monster Zones, and if you do, place that number of Season Counters on this card, also those zones cannot be used while this card is on the field. 
②: Monsters you control gain 400 ATK for each Season Counter on this card. 
③: Once per turn, during your opponent's End Phase: You can take 1 Field Spell from your Deck that you can place a Season Counter on, and place it face-up on your field (but neither player can activate its effects this turn), and if you do, place all Season Counters on this card on that card.

name: Anotherverse Stradios
desc: A god of war from another universe that has overcome countless wars. If this prestige be thy desire, come and try to take it.

name: Leo Wizard, the Dark Mage
desc:
You can only use the ③ effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: Monsters whose original Level is 4 or lower with more than 1350 ATK and/or DEF require 1 Tribute to Normal Summon from the hand.
②: At the start of the Damage Step, if this card battles a LIGHT monster: You can destroy that monster.
③: If this card is destroyed by battle or card effect: You can add 1 monster with 1350 ATK from your Deck to your hand.

name: Sky Striker Ace = Zero
desc:
2 "Sky Striker Ace" monsters
You can only Special Summon "Sky Striker Ace = Zero(s)" once per turn. Cannot be used as Link Material. You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card' name per turn, and only once that turn.
①: If this card is Special Summoned: You can add 1 "Sky Striker" Spell from your Deck or GY to your hand.
②: (Quick Effect): You can Tribute this card; Special Summon 1 "Sky Striker Ace – Raye" and 1 "Sky Striker Ace – Roze" from your Deck and/or GY, then you can destroy 1 card on the field.

name: Sky Striker Alternative – Lemnis Gate
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: Target an equal number of "Sky Striker Ace" monsters and "Sky Striker" Spells in your GY; shuffle them into the Deck, then you can return to the hand up to 1 card on the field for every 3 cards shuffled.
②: If a "Sky Striker" monster(s) is Special Summoned to your field while this card is in your GY: You can banish this card; immediately after this effect resolves, Link Summon 1 "Sky Striker Ace" monster.

name: Super Quantal Fairy Zetan
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is in your hand and you control a "Super Quant" monster other than "Super Quantal Fairy Zetan": You can Special Summon this card, then you can make its Level become the Level of 1 "Super Quant" monster you control.
②: You can Tribute this card and send 1 "Super Quant" card from your Deck to the GY, except a DARK monster; Special Summon 1 "Super Quant" monster from your Deck, except "Super Quantal Fairy Zetan".

name: Super Quantum Black Layer
desc:
You can only use the ①, ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: When your opponent activates a monster effect (Quick Effect): You can discard 1 other card, and if you do, Special Summon this card from your hand.
②: If this card is Special Summoned: You can Special Summon 1 "Super Quantal Mech Beast" Xyz Monster from your Extra Deck, by using this card you control as material (this is treated as an Xyz Summon), and if you do, attach 1 "Super Quant" monster from your GY to it as additional material.
③: If this card is sent to the GY: You can add 1 "Super Quant" Spell from your Deck to your hand.

name: Layer 19: "Preventing the Invasion! The Pitch-Black Super Quantum!!"
desc:
①: Activate 1 of these effects (but you can only use each effect of this card's name once per turn);
● Target 1 Attack Position monster; change it to Defense Position.
● If you control a "Super Quant" monster: Special Summon 1 "Super Quant" monster from your Deck in Defense Position, with a different original Attribute from the monsters you control.
● Set 1 "Super Quant" Trap from your Deck. It can be activated this turn.

name: Serene Psychic Girl
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can banish 1 card from your hand, and if you do, Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower Psychic monster from your Deck, except "Serene Psychic Girl", also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Psychic monsters.
②: You can target face-up monsters on the field that have a Level, up to the number of Psychic monsters you control; increase their Levels by 1 until the end of this turn.

name: Hushed Psychic Minister
desc:
You can only Special Summon with the ① effect of this card's name once per turn. You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If you control a Psychic monster other than "Hushed Psychic Minister", you can Special Summon this card (from your hand) in Defense Position
②: You can banish this card and 1 other Psychic monster from your GY, then target 1 face-up monster on the field; banish it until the End Phase.

name: Mind Procedure
desc:
You can only use 1 of the ① and ③ effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①: If this card is Special Summoned by a monster effect or Normal Summoned: You can pay 2000 LP; add 1 "Teleport" Normal or Quick-Play Spell from your Deck or GY to your hand.
②: If this card you control would be used as material for the Synchro Summon of a Psychic monster, you can treat it as a non-Tuner.
③: If this card becomes banished: You can pay 1000 LP; Special Summon it.

name: Prototype Psychic Blaster
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can discard this card; Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower Psychic monster from your hand or banishment.
②: If this card is in your GY: You can pay 1000 LP and banish 1 other Psychic monster from your GY; Special Summon this card, but banish it when it leaves the field.

name: Absolute Axon Kicker
desc:
1 Psychic Synchro Monster + 1 Synchro Monster
Must first be Fusion Summoned. You can only use the ③ effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If this card is Fusion Summoned: You can pay 2000 LP; banish all face-up cards your opponent controls.
②: Cannot be destroyed by card effects.
③: If this card is in your GY, except the turn it was sent there: You can banish it; Special Summon 1 Level 10 Psychic Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck. (This is treated as a Fusion Summon.)

name: Silent Psychic Magician
desc:
1 Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner monsters
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If this card is Special Summoned: You can target 1 Level 4 or lower Psychic monster in your GY or banishment; Special Summon it, then you can increase its Level by 1, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Psychic monsters.
②: If this card you control would be used as Synchro Material, you can treat it as a non-Tuner.

name: Thought Cross Archfiend
desc:
1 Psychic Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can target 1 of your banished Level 7 or lower Psychic monsters; Special Summon it.
②: During the Battle Phase (Quick Effect): You can Tribute 1 other monster; gain LP equal to its original ATK, and if you do, this card gains that much ATK until the end of this turn.

name: Psychic Blaster Mk-II
desc:
1 Psychic Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner Psychic monsters
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①: You can target 1 banished monster; Special Summon it to your field.
②: During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can banish 1 monster from your GY, then target 1 other face-up monster on the field; banish it, then gain LP equal to the banished monster's original ATK.

name: Parallel Teleport
desc:
You can only activate 1 card with this card name's per turn. You cannot Special Summon the turn you activate this card, except Psychic monsters.
①: Tribute 1 Psychic monster that has a Level; Special Summon 1 Level 7 or lower Psychic monster from your Deck or Extra Deck, then, if those monsters' original Levels are different, you lose LP equal to the difference x 1000.

name: Teleport Fusion
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: During the Main Phase: Fusion Summon 1 Psychic Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, by banishing Psychic monsters from your field and/or GY as material.
②: If your face-up Psychic monster(s) Special Summoned from the Extra Deck is destroyed by battle or card effect: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 of your banished Psychic monsters; Special Summon it.

name: Eidos the Underworld Monarch
desc:
You can only use the ①, ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can add 1 "Monarch" Spell/Trap or 1 monster with 2800 ATK/1000 DEF from your Deck or GY to your hand.
②: You can declare 1 Attribute; 1 face-up monster on the field becomes that Attribute.
③: If you Tribute Summon a monster with 2400 or more ATK/1000 DEF while this card is in your GY: You can either add this card to your hand or Special Summon it.

name: Tessera the Prime Squire
desc:
You can only use the ①, ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can reveal 1 "Monarch" Spell/Trap in your hand; Special Summon this card from your hand.
②: During your Main Phase, you can: Immediately after this effect resolves, Tribute Summon 1 monster.
③: If this card is sent to the GY: You can Special Summon 1 monster with 800 ATK/1000 DEF from your Deck, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn.

name: Scheme of the Monarchs
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: Send 1 "Monarch" Spell/Trap from your Deck to the GY, except "Scheme of the Monarchs".
②: If this card becomes banished: You can target 1 face-up monster your opponent controls; add 1 monster with 2400 ATK/1000 DEF and the same Attribute from your Deck or GY to your hand, then, immediately after this effect resolves, you can Normal Summon 1 "Zaborg the Thunder Monarch", "Mobius the Frost Monarch", "Thestalos the Firestorm Monarch", "Granmarg the Rock Monarch", "Raiza the Storm Monarch", or "Caius the Shadow Monarch".

name: Rebellion of the Monarchs
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: Discard 1 card; you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, also reveal 3 monsters with 800, or 2400 or more, ATK/1000 DEF from your Deck, your opponent chooses 1 for you to add to your hand, also send the rest to the GY.
②: You can banish this card from your GY; Special Summon 1 monster with 800 ATK/1000 DEF from your hand.

name: Culmination of the Monarchs
desc:
①: If your opponent Special Summons a monster(s) and you control a Tribute Summoned monster: You can banish 1 "Monarch" Spell/Trap from your GY, then activate 1 of these effects (but you can only use each effect of this card's name once per turn).
● Destroy 1 monster on the field.
● Destroy up to 2 Spells/Traps on the field.
● Discard 1 random card from your opponent's hand.
● Destroy 1 Set card.
● Place 1 card on the field on the top of the Deck.
● Banish 1 card on the field.

name: Invoked Magistus Omega
desc:
"Aleister the Invoker" + 1 Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, or Link Monster
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Special Summoned: You can target 1 Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, or Link Monster in your GY and 1 monster on the field; banish them.
②: If this Fusion Summoned card is destroyed by battle or card effect: You can Special Summon 1 Level 4 Spellcaster monster from your Deck, then you can equip this card to it as an Equip Spell that gives it 1000 ATK.

name: Zubababa Knight
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can activate 1 of these effects;
● Add 1 "Zubaba" monster from your Deck to your hand, except "Zubababa Knight", and if you do, this card's Level becomes that monster's.
● Destroy 1 opponent's Level 4 or lower Defense Position monster.
②: If this card is detached to activate an Xyz Monster's effect: You can add 1 "Gagaga" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Gagaga Ganbara Knight
desc:
You can only use the 1st and 2nd effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can reveal 1 "Gagaga" monster in your Extra Deck; Special Summon this card from your hand, then you can apply 1 of these effects.
● Special Summon 1 "Gagaga" monster from your hand.
● Change the battle position of 1 monster on the field.
②: If this card is detached to activate an Xyz Monster's effect: You can add 1 "Gogogo" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Gogogo Goblindbergh
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: When this card is Normal Summoned: You can activate this effect; you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Xyz Monsters, also Special Summon 1 non-Warrior "Gogogo" monster from your hand, Deck, or GY, then, if this card is in Attack Position, change it to Defense Position.
②: If this card is detached to activate an Xyz Monster's effect: You can add 1 "Dododo" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Dodododo Warrior
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: You can send 1 "Dododo" monster from your Deck to the GY; you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Xyz Monsters, also Special Summon this card from your hand, but its Level becomes 4 and its ATK becomes 1800.
②: If this card is detached to activate an Xyz Monster's effect: You can add 1 "Zubaba" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Number F0: Utopic Future Zexal
desc:
2 Xyz Monsters with the same Rank
(This card's original Rank is always treated as 1.)
①: Gains ATK/DEF equal to the total Ranks of all Xyz Monsters you control and in your opponent's GY x 500.
②: Your opponent's monsters cannot target monsters for attacks, except this one, also your opponent cannot target other cards on the field with card effects.
③: Once per turn, when your opponent activates a card or effect on the field (Quick Effect): You can detach 1 material from this card; take control of 1 monster your opponent controls, also this card cannot be destroyed by battle or card effects this turn.

name: Gagagaga Girl
desc:
2 Level 4 monsters
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①: If this card has a "Zubaba", "Gagaga", "Gogogo", and/or "Dododo" card as material: You can detach 1 material from this card; add 1 "Gagaga", "Onomato", or "Xyz" card from your Deck to your hand.
②: An "Utopic Future" Xyz Monster that has this card as material gains this effect.
● If it is Xyz Summoned: Activate this effect; it can make a second attack during each Battle Phase this turn.

name: Heroic Champion – Magnum Excalibur
desc:
2 Level 4 Warrior monsters
①: If this card battles an opponent's monster, during damage calculation: You can detach 2 materials from this card; this card's current ATK becomes doubled during damage calculation only.
②: Once per turn, during the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can target 1 other face-up monster you control; equip this card you control to that target as an Equip Spell that makes it gain 2000 ATK/DEF.
③: You can banish this card from your GY; shuffle 3 Warrior monsters from your GY into the Deck.

name: Gagaga Hope Tactics
desc:
You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: "Utopia" or "Utopic" Xyz Monsters you control whose original Attribute is LIGHT cannot be destroyed by card effects, also your opponent cannot target them with card effects.
②: You can declare a Level from 1 to 12 and target 2 face-up monsters you control, including a "Gagaga" monster; their Levels become the declared Level.
③: If you Xyz Summon an "Utopia" or "Utopic" Xyz Monster whose original Attribute is LIGHT: You can target 1 card your opponent controls; destroy it.

name: Xyz Unbreakable Barrier
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①: When a Spell/Trap Card, or monster effect, is activated and you control an Xyz Monster: Negate the activation, then you can detach 2 materials from your monsters, then destroy 1 card on the field.
②: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 Xyz Monster you control; attach 1 LIGHT "Utopia" or "Utopic" Xyz Monster from your GY to it as material.

name: Saiba the Fighting Swordsmith
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's each name once per turn.
①: You can target 1 Level 6 or lower Warrior monster in your GY; Special Summon it (but its effects are negated), also this card cannot be used as Synchro Material for the rest of this turn.
②: During your opponent's Main Phase, you can (Quick Effect): Immediately after this effect resolves, Synchro Summon using a Warrior monster you control as material.

name: Stinger the Electric Expeller
desc: A member of the Dune Defense Force who manage to keep repelling the foreign invaders, thanks to their heroic efforts. His sword is supposed to be wielded only for the sake of protecting those he wishes to protect.
